{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775836281215,"sessionID":"ses_287eaa4dfffe6ByyA3ZuLglM2s","part":{"id":"prt_d78162333001CQYs3SQ7K4CRTy","messageID":"msg_d78161c8d001y6mV8R1Be0dqWt","sessionID":"ses_287eaa4dfffe6ByyA3ZuLglM2s","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_8095ad2521de4a27bb59b387","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis document specifies the Valkey backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n\n### 1.2 Valkey Data Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    valkeyStore                          │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  cli: valkey.Client                               │  │\n│  │  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 │  │\n│  │  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           │  │\n│  │  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    │  │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘\n                        │\n                        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Valkey Server                      │\n│                                                         │\n│  String Keys:                                           │\n│    session:{sessionID} → JSON(SandboxInfo)              │\n│                                                         │\n│  Sorted Sets:                                           │\n│    session:expiry          ZSET { sessionID: score }    │\n│      score = ExpiresAt.Unix()                           │\n│                                                         │\n│    session:last_activity   ZSET { sessionID: score }    │\n│      score = lastActivityAt.Unix()                      │\n│                                                         │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.3 Package Layout\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go                  # Store interface (shared)\n├── singleton.go              # Provider selection (shared)\n├── store_valkey.go           # Valkey implementation ← AR-014\n├── store_valkey_test.go      # Valkey unit tests ← AR-014\n└── codec.go                  # JSON encode/decode helpers (shared)\n```\n\n### 1.4 Dependencies\n\n| Module | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client library |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | — | `SandboxInfo` type |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Model\n\n### 2.1 Valkey Store Struct\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Key Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session JSON string keys |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry-based GC queries |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity-based GC queries |\n\n### 2.3 Valkey Key Patterns\n\n| Key Pattern | Type | Content |\n|-------------|------|---------|\n| `session:{sessionID}` | String | JSON-marshaled `SandboxInfo` |\n| `session:expiry` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n| `session:last_activity` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `LastActivityAt.Unix()` |\n\n### 2.4 SandboxInfo JSON Schema\n\nIdentical to AR-013 Redis implementation. Stored as JSON string at `session:{sessionID}`.\n\n### 2.5 Sorted Set Score Semantics\n\n| Index | Score Source | When Written |\n|-------|-------------|--------------|\n| `session:expiry` | `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n| `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n| `session:last_activity` | `float64(at.Unix())` or `time.Now()` | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Interfaces\n\n### 3.1 Store Interface Implementation\n\n`valkeyStore` implements the same `Store` interface as `redisStore`:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Method Specifications\n\nMethod specifications are identical to AR-013 Redis implementation, with Valkey-specific command mappings:\n\n| Redis Command | Valkey Equivalent | Notes |\n|---------------|-------------------|-------|\n| `PING` | `PING` | Same |\n| `GET` | `GET` | Same |\n| `SETNX` | `SET NX` | Same semantics |\n| `SET XX` | `SET XX` | Same semantics |\n| `DEL` | `DEL` | Same |\n| `ZADD` | `ZADD` | Same |\n| `ZREM` | `ZREM` | Same |\n| `ZRANGEBYSCORE` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE` | Same |\n| `MGET` | `MGET` | Same |\n| `EXISTS` | `EXISTS` | Same |\n\n### 3.3 Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc newValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, error) {\n    valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n\n    valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if valkeyPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n\n    cli, err := valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{InitAddress: []string{valkeyAddr}, Password: valkeyPassword})\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"valkey client creation failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    if err := cli.Do(context.Background(), cli.B().Ping().Build()).Error(); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"valkey ping failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    return &valkeyStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 3.4 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | — | Valkey server address |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | — | Auth password |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `valkey` for this backend |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\nIdentical to AR-013 Redis implementation. Valkey client errors propagate with context.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\nTest cases mirror AR-013 Redis tests with Valkey-specific setup:\n\n| Test Name | Description | Assertions |\n|-----------|-------------|------------|\n| `TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success` | PING → PONG | `require.NoError` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Ping_Failure` | Bad connection | `assert.Error` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found` | Store then get | `assert.Equal` on SessionID |\n| `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Missing key | `assert.ErrorIs(ErrNotFound)` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success` | Full pipeline | Key exists, ZSET members added |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected` | nil input | `assert.Error` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` | Zero ExpiresAt | `assert.Error` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Idempotent` | Double store | Second call doesn't overwrite |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` | SETXX updates | JSON changed, ZSET unchanged |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | No prior store | `assert.Error` contains \"key not exists\" |\n| `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Full cleanup | Key deleted, ZSET members removed |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` | Query by expiry | Returns expired, not active |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ZeroLimit` | limit=0 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanMember` | ZSET member without key | Skipped, not error |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` | Query by activity | Returns inactive, not active |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_Success` | Valid session | ZADD with new score |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound` | Missing session | `assert.ErrorIs(ErrNotFound)` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` | `at.IsZero()` | Uses `time.Now()` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptyID` | Empty sessionID | `assert.Error` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Close` | Connection closed | No error |\n\n### 5.2 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n5. No sensitive data in logs (passwords, connection strings)\n6. Test coverage ≥ 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Deployment Considerations\n\n### 6.1 Connection Pooling\n\nvalkey-go uses its own connection pooling. Default settings should suffice for initial deployment.\n\n### 6.2 Password Policy\n\nPassword required by default. Set `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments.\n\n### 6.3 ZSET Index Growth\n\nIdentical to Redis implementation. GC controller must regularly clean up expired/inactive sessions.\n\n### 6.4 Memory Considerations\n\nIdentical to Redis implementation: ~700 bytes × number of active sessions.\n\n### 6.5 Valkey Cluster\n\nFor Valkey Cluster deployments:\n- Consider hash tags for key slot affinity: `session:{cluster}:{sessionID}`\n- `MGET` in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` requires keys in same slot\n- Monitor `CROSSSLOT` errors\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Steps\n\n### Phase 1: Core Implementation (Day 1)\n\n1. Implement `valkeyStore` struct in `store_valkey.go`\n2. Implement constructor with environment variable validation\n3. Implement `Ping`, `Close`, `sessionKey` helper\n\n### Phase 2: CRUD Operations (Day 2)\n\n1. Implement `StoreSandbox` with pipeline\n2. Implement `UpdateSandbox` with SET XX\n3. Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` with pipeline\n4. Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID` with ErrNotFound handling\n\n### Phase 3: Query Operations (Day 3)\n\n1. Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n2. Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes`\n3. Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n4. Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n\n### Phase 4: Testing & Validation (Day 4)\n\n1. Write unit tests\n2. Run `go test -race ./pkg/store/...`\n3. Verify test coverage\n4. Fix all issues\n\n---\n\n## 8. Future Changes\n\n| Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n| AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n\n### Known Limitations\n\n- No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n- `MGET` in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` assumes single-slot keys for cluster deployments\n- No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n- `SET NX` in `StoreSandbox` prevents updates; use `UpdateSandbox` for modifications\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","time":{"start":1775836281203,"end":1775836281212}}}}
